## Set up Firebase Authentication in Next.js App Router

### 1. Create a Firebase project
- Go to console.firebase.google.com → Add project → follow the wizard.
- In the left sidebar, click **Build → Authentication → Get started**.
- Enable the sign-in methods you need: **Email/Password** and/or **Google**.
- In **Project settings → General**, scroll down to **Your apps** → click the web icon `</>` → register your app → note the `firebaseConfig` object.

### 2. Install packages
```bash
npm install firebase firebase-admin
```
- `firebase` is the client-side modular SDK (v9+).
- `firebase-admin` is the server-side SDK used to verify session cookies in Server Components and Route Handlers.

### 3. Add environment variables
Add to `.env.local`:
```
# Client-side (safe to expose — values are public)
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY=AIza...
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project.firebaseapp.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-project.appspot.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=1234567890
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_APP_ID=1:1234567890:web:abc123

# Server-side only (NEVER expose to client)
FIREBASE_ADMIN_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
FIREBASE_ADMIN_CLIENT_EMAIL=firebase-adminsdk@your-project.iam.gserviceaccount.com
FIREBASE_ADMIN_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\n...\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"
```
- Get Admin credentials from Firebase Console → Project settings → Service accounts → Generate new private key.
- IMPORTANT: The private key contains literal `\n` characters. In `.env.local`, wrap it in double quotes and use `\n` escape sequences (not actual newlines).

### 4. Create the Firebase client singleton
Create `src/lib/firebase/client.ts`:
```ts
import { initializeApp, getApps } from 'firebase/app';
import { getAuth } from 'firebase/auth';

const firebaseConfig = {
  apiKey: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY,
  authDomain: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN,
  projectId: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID,
  storageBucket: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET,
  messagingSenderId: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID,
  appId: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_APP_ID,
};

const app = getApps().length === 0 ? initializeApp(firebaseConfig) : getApps()[0];
export const auth = getAuth(app);
export default app;
```
- IMPORTANT: The `getApps().length === 0` guard prevents re-initializing the app on every hot reload in dev mode.

### 5. Create the Firebase Admin singleton
Create `src/lib/firebase/admin.ts`:
```ts
import { cert, getApps, initializeApp } from 'firebase-admin/app';
import { getAuth } from 'firebase-admin/auth';

const adminApp = getApps().find(a => a.name === 'admin') ??
  initializeApp(
    {
      credential: cert({
        projectId: process.env.FIREBASE_ADMIN_PROJECT_ID,
        clientEmail: process.env.FIREBASE_ADMIN_CLIENT_EMAIL,
        privateKey: process.env.FIREBASE_ADMIN_PRIVATE_KEY?.replace(/\\n/g, '\n'),
      }),
    },
    'admin'
  );

export const adminAuth = getAuth(adminApp);
```
- IMPORTANT: The `.replace(/\\n/g, '\n')` transforms the escaped newlines from the env var back into real newlines. Without this, `cert()` throws a parsing error.
- IMPORTANT: Name the Admin app `'admin'` to avoid clashing with the default client app when both run in the same process (e.g., in Route Handlers).

### 6. Implement sign-in — Google OAuth
Create `src/components/sign-in-button.tsx`:
```ts
'use client';
import { signInWithPopup, GoogleAuthProvider } from 'firebase/auth';
import { auth } from '@/lib/firebase/client';

export function SignInWithGoogle() {
  async function handleSignIn() {
    const provider = new GoogleAuthProvider();
    const result = await signInWithPopup(auth, provider);
    // Send the ID token to your server to create a session cookie
    const idToken = await result.user.getIdToken();
    await fetch('/api/auth/session', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({ idToken }),
    });
    window.location.href = '/dashboard';
  }

  return <button onClick={handleSignIn}>Sign in with Google</button>;
}
```

### 7. Implement sign-in — Email/Password
```ts
'use client';
import { signInWithEmailAndPassword, createUserWithEmailAndPassword } from 'firebase/auth';
import { auth } from '@/lib/firebase/client';

export async function signIn(email: string, password: string) {
  const result = await signInWithEmailAndPassword(auth, email, password);
  const idToken = await result.user.getIdToken();
  await fetch('/api/auth/session', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
    body: JSON.stringify({ idToken }),
  });
}

export async function signUp(email: string, password: string) {
  const result = await createUserWithEmailAndPassword(auth, email, password);
  const idToken = await result.user.getIdToken();
  await fetch('/api/auth/session', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
    body: JSON.stringify({ idToken }),
  });
}
```

### 8. Create the session API Route Handler
Create `src/app/api/auth/session/route.ts`:
```ts
import { adminAuth } from '@/lib/firebase/admin';
import { NextRequest, NextResponse } from 'next/server';
import { cookies } from 'next/headers';

const SESSION_DURATION_MS = 60 * 60 * 24 * 5 * 1000; // 5 days

export async function POST(req: NextRequest) {
  const { idToken } = await req.json();

  try {
    const sessionCookie = await adminAuth.createSessionCookie(idToken, {
      expiresIn: SESSION_DURATION_MS,
    });
    const cookieStore = await cookies();
    cookieStore.set('session', sessionCookie, {
      maxAge: SESSION_DURATION_MS / 1000,
      httpOnly: true,
      secure: process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production',
      sameSite: 'lax',
      path: '/',
    });
    return NextResponse.json({ ok: true });
  } catch {
    return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Invalid token' }, { status: 401 });
  }
}

export async function DELETE() {
  const cookieStore = await cookies();
  cookieStore.delete('session');
  return NextResponse.json({ ok: true });
}
```

### 9. Verify the session in Server Components
Create `src/lib/firebase/session.ts`:
```ts
import { cookies } from 'next/headers';
import { adminAuth } from './admin';

export async function getSession() {
  const cookieStore = await cookies();
  const sessionCookie = cookieStore.get('session')?.value;
  if (!sessionCookie) return null;
  try {
    return await adminAuth.verifySessionCookie(sessionCookie, true);
  } catch {
    return null;
  }
}
```
Use in any Server Component or Server Action:
```ts
import { getSession } from '@/lib/firebase/session';
import { redirect } from 'next/navigation';

export default async function DashboardPage() {
  const session = await getSession();
  if (!session) redirect('/login');
  return <div>Welcome {session.email}</div>;
}
```

### 10. Add middleware for route protection
Create `src/middleware.ts`:
```ts
import { NextRequest, NextResponse } from 'next/server';

export async function middleware(req: NextRequest) {
  const session = req.cookies.get('session')?.value;
  const isProtected = req.nextUrl.pathname.startsWith('/dashboard');
  if (isProtected && !session) {
    return NextResponse.redirect(new URL('/login', req.url));
  }
  return NextResponse.next();
}

export const config = {
  matcher: ['/dashboard/:path*'],
};
```
- IMPORTANT: Middleware cannot use `firebase-admin` directly because the Admin SDK uses Node.js APIs incompatible with the Edge Runtime. For full cookie verification in middleware, use a lightweight JWT library or switch middleware runtime to Node.js with `export const runtime = 'nodejs'`.

### 11. Sign out
```ts
// Client component
'use client';
import { signOut } from 'firebase/auth';
import { auth } from '@/lib/firebase/client';

export function SignOutButton() {
  async function handleSignOut() {
    await signOut(auth);
    await fetch('/api/auth/session', { method: 'DELETE' });
    window.location.href = '/login';
  }
  return <button onClick={handleSignOut}>Sign out</button>;
}
```

### 12. Test the full flow
- Run `npm run dev`.
- Click Google Sign-In → complete OAuth → confirm `/dashboard` loads.
- Open DevTools → Application → Cookies → verify `session` cookie is set as `httpOnly`.
- Refresh the page → confirm the session persists without a client-side sign-in call.
- Sign out → confirm you are redirected to `/login`.

### Common errors & fixes
- **`Firebase: Error (auth/configuration-not-found)`** — Your `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY` or `authDomain` is missing or wrong. Double-check against the Firebase console config object.
- **`admin.createSessionCookie` throws `INVALID_ARGUMENT`** — The ID token expired (they last 1 hour). Refresh it with `user.getIdToken(true)` before sending to the server.
- **`PEM routines: PEM_read_bio: no start line` in Admin SDK** — The private key's `\n` escape sequences were not converted to real newlines. Add `.replace(/\\n/g, '\n')` when reading `FIREBASE_ADMIN_PRIVATE_KEY`.
- **`FirebaseApp named 'admin' already exists`** — Remove `initializeApp()` call from module scope and use the singleton guard in Step 5.
- **Google sign-in popup blocked** — The popup was triggered outside a direct user interaction (e.g., inside a `useEffect`). Always call `signInWithPopup` directly from an `onClick` handler.
- **Session cookie not sent on HTTPS** — You set `secure: true` but your dev server uses HTTP. Add a condition: `secure: process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production'`.
- **`verifySessionCookie` throws on every request** — The session cookie was created with a mismatched project ID. Confirm `FIREBASE_ADMIN_PROJECT_ID` matches the project that issued the ID token.
- **Middleware redirect loop** — Your `/login` page is inside the protected matcher pattern. Make sure `/login` is excluded from the matcher.

### What NOT to do
- Do NOT expose `FIREBASE_ADMIN_PRIVATE_KEY` or `FIREBASE_ADMIN_CLIENT_EMAIL` to the client — prefix only safe values with `NEXT_PUBLIC_`. Admin credentials give full read/write access to all Firebase services.
- Do NOT call `initializeApp()` unconditionally at module scope — it will throw `'Firebase app named "[DEFAULT]" already exists'` on hot reloads. Always guard with `getApps().length === 0`.
- Do NOT verify ID tokens on every request using `adminAuth.verifyIdToken()` — ID tokens expire after 1 hour and refreshing them requires a client round-trip. Use session cookies (`createSessionCookie` / `verifySessionCookie`) which can last up to 2 weeks.
- Do NOT use Firebase Auth without server-side session cookies in an App Router project — if you only track auth state client-side, Server Components have no way to know who is logged in.
- Do NOT put Firebase Admin SDK imports in Client Components — `firebase-admin` uses Node.js built-ins (`crypto`, `fs`) that are not available in the browser bundle.
- Do NOT use `signInWithRedirect` in Next.js App Router — the redirect flow loses React state and causes hydration mismatches; use `signInWithPopup` instead.
- Do NOT use Firebase Realtime Database as a substitute for Auth session management — Auth and database are separate Firebase services with separate security rules.
- Do NOT skip revoking sessions on sensitive security events — call `adminAuth.revokeRefreshTokens(uid)` when a user changes their password or is banned.
